        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 6:05PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 605 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Simla, or 23 miles southwest of Limon, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Simla.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
